While VAT, the proposed Sovereign Wealth Fund (SWF), and the State Bank are the expected focal points for Wednesday’s budget speech, finalists in the annual budget speech competition believe job cuts are imminent. Speaking to the Citizen in Cape Town on Tuesday, all were in agreement that job cuts have become absolutely necessary in order to provide the wiggle room needed to move forward. “For us to pursue efficiency, you have to skim some fat. Jobs are one of the things that are going to be skimmed in order for us to achieve our long-term goals and sustainability,” said University...